The benchmark  BUX (BUX)  index rose 0.3
percent to 16,990.10 by the close in Budapest, extending its
advance in the past two days to 3.6 percent.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Est Media Nyrt. (ESTMEDIA HB), a Hungarian entertainment
company, gained the most in three months after saying it plans
to issue three-year convertible bonds for a unit that organizes
music festivals. The shares jumped 15 percent to 46 forint.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTELEKOM HB), the Hungarian unit of
Deutsche Telekom AG, rose 1.6 percent to 444 forint as European
stocks rallied after  China  cut  interest rates  for the first time
since 2008 to bolster growth in the worldâ€™s second-largest
